hes%20and%20the%20need%20for%20sustained%20focus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Docket%20cofounder%20Boris%20Skurikhin's%20YC%20cohort%2C%20he%20said%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyc-founders-younger-under-more-pressure-beacause-ai-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eyounger%20founders%3C%2Fa%3E%20often%20spoke%20about%20having%20to%20%26quot%3Block%20in.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20entails%20the%20person%20working%20long%20hours%20and%20foregoing%20any%20extravagant%20social%20interaction%20and%20drinking%2C%26quot%3B%20Skurikhin%20said.%20%26quot%3BEspecially%20during%20the%20batch%2C%20some%20people%20made%20it%20a%20pact%20to%20only%20dedicate%20their%20time%20to%20sleeping%20and%20working.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESkurikhin%20is%2025%20and%20drinks%20occasionally.%20The%20most%20fervent%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Blocked%20in%26quot%3B%20fully%20sober%20crowd%2C%20he%20said%2C%20was%20around%2021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFort%20cofounder%20Miranda%20Nover%20said%20that%20image%20was%20important%20to%20these%20entrepreneurs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20were%20a%20software%20founder%2C%20a%20B2B%20SAAS%20founder%2C%20an%20AI%20founder%2C%20you%20were%20definitely%20trying%20to%20signal%3A%20We're%20doing%20this%20six%20days%20a%20week%20in-office%2C%20we're%20working%20until%209%20p.m.%2C%20we're%20not%20drinking%2C%20we're%20not%20partying%2C%20we%20don't%20do%20any%20of%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENover%20said%20that%20might%20be%20shifting.%20As%20people%20pay%20more%20attention%20to%20%26quot%3Bconsumer%20distribution%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bmimetic%20value%20of%20founders%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20there%20may%20be%20a%20renewed%20focus%20on%20sociability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECyril%20Gorlla%2C%20cofounder%20of%20CTGT%2C%20considers%20drinking%20to%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bpoison.%26quot%3B%20He%20described%20workweeks%20of%2080-90%20hours%2C%20something%20that%20drinking%20would%20inhibit.%20%26quot%3BWe%20say%2C%20'your%20body's%20a%20temple%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGorlla%20hit%20on%20another%20common%20reason%20for%20the%20drinking%20slowdown%20in%20the%20Valley%3A%20An%20increased%20focus%20on%20health.%20Founders%20who%20spoke%20to%20Business%20Insider%20listed%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-pick-right-supplements-doctors-7-step-daily-routine-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esupplements%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20showed%20off%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foura-ring-fitness-tracker-pros-cons-after-years-wearing-style-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EOura%20rings%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Multiple%20founders%20mentioned%20popular%20health-focused%20personalities%20like%20longevity-obsessed%20Bryan%20Johnson%2C%20founder%20of%20Braintree%2C%20who%20now%20says%20he's%20alcohol%20free%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-exec-bryan-johnson-used-to-drink-alcohol-for-breakfast-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egiving%20up%20a%20daily%203-oz%20glass%20of%20wine%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20of%20the%2071%20calories%20it%20contained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKieran%20White%2C%20cofounder%20of%20Curo%2C%20said%20he's%20been%20sober%20since%20he%20was%20young.%20He%20compared%20being%20a%20founder%20to%20being%20a%20professional%20athlete.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20always%20have%20to%20perform%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhite's%20cofounder%2C%20Andrew%20Porter%2C%20still%20drinks%2C%20sipping%20on%20an%20IPA%20where%20he%20can%20find%20them.%20But%20he%20said%20he's%20cut%20back%2C%20only%20drinking%20at%20VC%20and%20networking%20events.%20He's%20not%20partying%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20in%20grind%20mode%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Porter%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20could%20also%20be%20regional%20influences.%20California%20has%20long%20been%20a%20hot%20spot%20for%20health%20trends%2C%20especially%20in